cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper studies the resilience of power distribution, which can be considered a control problem. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses external hazards and large-scale power failures, which can be related to security and cryptography. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper uses mathematical models and approximations to study the resilience of power distribution. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper uses real data from the electric grid to learn time-varying model parameters and the resilience metric. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper studies the ability of power distribution to remain operational and recover rapidly upon failures, which can be related to performance.
